data-triple-N3.o: "The Korean alphabet, also known as Hangul, or Chosongul (officially transcribed Han-geul in South Korea and Choson'gul in North Korea), is the native alphabet of the Korean language. It was created during the Joseon Dynasty in 1443, and is now the official script of both North Korea and South Korea, and co-official in the Yanbian Korean Autonomous Prefecture of China's Jilin Province."@en
